  2.4 istio-wasm-analysis.md — The actual measurement record

  This is the substantive findings document. Structure and content:

  Baseline (pre-modification) — k top po -n istio-system:
  - istio-internal-istio pods ~50m CPU / ~218 Mi.
  - istio-istio (public gateway) pods ~28m CPU / ~270 Mi.
  - Baseline CPU flamegraphs attached: sdk-internal-normal.svg, sdk-normal.svg.

  Test criteria — same six-stage profile; full inline k6 script that hits corePaths (4 SDK paths) and crashesPaths (1 healthcheck). Thresholds: p95<2000, p99<5000, error
  rate <10%, RPS>100.

  Run 1 — Sequential WasmPlugin (original) at spike (~50k RPS, mislabeled in section header as "333 VUs"):
  - 10 public-gateway pods.
  - 7 pods at ~2 cores, 3 pods at ~1.5 cores. Memory ~280–325 Mi.
  - Establishes the pain point: at peak, the gateway burns ~17 cores collectively executing the Wasm filter sequentially.

  Run 2 — "Grouping" modified WasmPlugin:
  - Light load (1k RPS, 5m): 4 pods at ~1.5 cores already hot, 6 new pods spun up by HPA; flamegraph perf10.svg.
  - Heavy (10k RPS, 10m): all 10 pods at ~1 core; flamegraph perf11.svg.
  - Spike (50k RPS) beginning: all 10 pods ~2 cores; flamegraph perf12.svg.
  - Spike peak: 7 pods ~2 cores, 3 pods ~1.5 cores — comparable to the sequential peak but reached only at full 50k RPS. Comment: "reach the sequential wasm plugin
  version" — i.e., grouping pushes the cliff out, doesn't eliminate it.

  Run 3 — Grouping + Internal Regex checks:
  - Light (1k RPS, 5m): only 4 pods needed, each ~1.5 cores.
  - Heavy (10k RPS, 10m): 8 pods at ~1 core (fewer pods than Run 2 for the same load).
  - Spike (50k RPS): 10 pods — 4 at ~2 cores, 6 at ~1.5 cores (better distribution than Run 2's 7/3 split).

  Throughput comparison (Grafana, RPM per service):

  ┌─────────┬────────────┬────────────────────┬───────────────────────────┐
  │ Service │ Sequential │      Grouping      │ Grouping + Internal Regex │
  ├─────────┼────────────┼────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ Core    │ 28.8k RPM  │ 54.5k RPM (+13k)   │ 59.7k RPM (+5.2k)         │
  ├─────────┼────────────┼────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ Crashes │ 57.7k RPM  │ 81.5k RPM (+23.8k) │ 97.0k RPM (+15.5k)        │
  └─────────┴────────────┴────────────────────┴───────────────────────────┘

