  3. Profiled the original (sequential) WasmPlugin under spike load. Documented the ~2-core-per-pod cost at 50k RPS across 10 public-gateway pods. Flamegraphs perf*.svg
  and perf*.stacks captured here.
  4. Iterated WasmPlugin v2 — grouping. Re-ran the full 21-minute profile, captured perf10/11/12.svg. Result: large RPM gains (Core +13k, Crashes +23.8k) but CPU still
  saturates at the 50k-RPS spike.
  5. Iterated WasmPlugin v3 — grouping + internal regex checks. Re-ran the profile. Result: further RPM gains (Core +5.2k, Crashes +15.5k), better pod-CPU distribution,
  and same load served with fewer pods at the 10k-RPS plateau.
  6. Logged the comparative outcome in the throughput table inside istio-wasm-analysis.md.

