  4. Key Takeaways from the Markdown Set

  - The three operator-facing docs (QUICK-START, README-LOAD-TEST, SETUP-GUIDE) overlap heavily — they're tiered runbooks (5-min / reference / full setup) for the same
  harness. The canonical load profile is identical across all three.
  - The real research output is istio-wasm-analysis.md: it shows that grouping routes inside the WasmPlugin nearly doubled Core RPM and added ~24k RPM on Crashes, and
  that adding internal regex checks on top of grouping further reduced pod-count at the 10k-RPS plateau and added another ~15k RPM on Crashes.
  - The 50k-RPS spike still saturates 10 gateway pods at ~2 cores even with both optimisations — i.e., this is now the next ceiling to attack.
  - Supporting artifacts in the same directory but not in the markdown: core-render-wasmplugin.yaml (rendered output), nine perf*.svg flamegraphs, four *.stacks files, k6
   test resources, and PNG screenshots of Grafana panels (core-request-metrics.png, crashes.png, *2pro.png, test-before-grouping.png, test-after-grouping.png).